title="Alex Nelson">Alex Nelson</fr:link></fr:author></fr:authors></fr:frontmatter><fr:mainmatter><fr:p>Let <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[R]]></fr:tex> be a <fr:link
type="local"
href="ra-0003.xml"
addr="ra-0003"
title="Commutative Ring">Commutative Ring</fr:link>. Let <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[a,b\in  R]]></fr:tex> with <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[b\neq 0]]></fr:tex>. A <html:dfn
xmlns:html="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">Greatest Common Divisor</html:dfn> of <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[a]]></fr:tex> and <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[b]]></fr:tex> is a nonzero element <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[d\in  R]]></fr:tex> such that:
<fr:ol><fr:li>It's a common <fr:link
type="local"
href="ra-001Q.xml"
addr="ra-001Q"
title="Divisor">divisor</fr:link>: <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[d\mathrel {\bigm |} a]]></fr:tex> and <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[d\mathrel {\bigm |} b]]></fr:tex>, and</fr:li>
<fr:li>It's greatest: for any <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[d'\in  R]]></fr:tex> such that <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[d'\mathrel {\bigm |} a]]></fr:tex> and <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[d'\mathrel {\bigm |} b]]></fr:tex>, we have <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[d'\mathrel {\bigm |} d]]></fr:tex>.</fr:li></fr:ol>
A greatest common divisor of <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[a]]></fr:tex> and <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[b]]></fr:tex> is denoted by <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\gcd (a,b)]]></fr:tex> or (abusing notation) by <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[(a,b)]]></fr:tex>.</fr:p>
 
   
